                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 534/17.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Stutesman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-07-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reports that there was a hostile demonstration in La Paz on Saturday and Sunday
                    last on account of decision of the Argentine Republic acting as arbitrator in
                    the boundary dispute between Bolivia and Peru. Says the Argentine and Peruvian
                    legations and Peruvian business houses were attacked by mobs, but no one was
                    seriously injured and very little property destroyed. Adds that the mob is under
                    control, and that the situation is now tranquil.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
